==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Postposition
<hw>Post`po*si"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>postposition</ets>. See <er>Postpone</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of placing after, or the state of being placed after.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>postposition</xex> of the nominative case to the
verb.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Mede.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1120 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A word or particle placed after, or at the end of,
another word; -- distinguished from <xex>preposition</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Postpositional</ent>⟦br⟧
